description:
In this episode, we learn about the short life of Annie Smith. She made a significant contribution in the early days of the Seventh Day Adventist church. She was a gifted writer, poet, and editor, and although her life was tragically cut short, she made a huge impact in early Adventism. Shunning a life of ease and plenty, she sacrificed worldly ambition and riches to work for little financial gain in the early days at our fledgling press.
